    <item>
      <title>git restore beats git reset</title>
      <link>https://ikhsanhaikal.com/til/git-restore-vs-reset/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ikhsanhaikal.com/til/git-restore-vs-reset/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;For months I reached for &lt;code&gt;reset HEAD&lt;/code&gt; to unstage files. It works — but it&amp;rsquo;s the wrong tool. Git 2.23 added &lt;code&gt;restore&lt;/code&gt; specifically for index and working-tree operations:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# unstage — keep working tree changes&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git restore --staged file.txt&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# discard working tree changes&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git restore file.txt&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# both at once&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git restore --staged --worktree file.txt&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The key distinction: &lt;em&gt;reset moves HEAD&lt;/em&gt; — it can rewrite history with &lt;code&gt;--hard&lt;/code&gt; and blow away your work. &lt;em&gt;restore&lt;/em&gt; only touches the index or working tree. Much safer for day-to-day use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
